\mathbb{R}
\mathbb{R}
n\in\mathbb{N}
p
f(x)=\left\{\begin{array}{rcl} 0 &\mbox{if} & x\leq 0 \\ \exp\left(-\frac{1}{x^2}\right)&\mbox{if}&x>0\end{array}\right.
\frac{d^n}{dx^n}\exp\left(-1/x^2\right) = p(1/x) \exp\left(-1/x^2\right)
\lim_{x\to 0^+} \frac{d^n}{dx^n}\exp\left(-1/x^2\right) = \lim_{z\to +\infty} p(z)\,e^{-z^2} = 0.
